      <note type="public_message">Dear Mabel: Have you the book with the piece I spoke the winter I went to Maud commencing as follows: I remember the bright June morning that they brought me home from the store and hung me up here in the kitchen close to the pantry door." If so could you please write it off and send it to me by return mail. would be very thankful to you. We have [speaking] so often and wish for good pieces. Am just fine. How is school? Canadian winter is just fine so far, hardly any stormy weather. Havn't had hardly any cold weather either. Learned to skate. Wish you were. How soon are you and Mary coming? Ha! I am looking for you every day. Don't disappoint me. Must close. Yours as ever, Kathryn M. Royer. If you can send any other pieces I'd be thankful.</note>
